{"questionId":"9070269","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>This question is about ethene, C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>4</sub>, and ethyne, C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>2</sub>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Ethyne reacts with chlorine in a similar way to ethene. Formulate equations for the following reactions.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/2a34556980b0ed205c30002d199ade305e438540.png\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>ethyne:</em> C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>2</sub> +&nbsp;Cl<sub>2</sub> →&nbsp;CHClCHCl</p>\n<p><em>benzene:</em> C<sub>6</sub>H<sub>6</sub> +&nbsp;Cl<sub>2</sub> →&nbsp;C<sub>6</sub>H<sub>5</sub>Cl +&nbsp;HCl</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept “C</em><sub><em>2</em></sub><em>H</em><sub><em>2</em></sub><em>Cl</em><sub><em>2</em></sub><em>”.</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9070269","referenceCode":"18M.2.hl.TZ1.b","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Ethyne reacts with chlorine in a similar way to ethene. Formulate equations for the following reactions.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry","10.2 Functional group chemistry","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}